You have until the end of January to make your views known. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A multiparty committee has recommended to Parliament that section 25 be amended to allow for land expropriation without compensation. However, ad-hoc committee chairperson, Dr Mathole Motshekga, says it will seek the public's opinion until the end of January before any decisions are made. "Upon receipt of all the input and submissions, the committee will also hold public hearings to listen to all our people regardless of their standing in society." Watch the full interview with Dr Mathole Motshekga above.